text: The SP Design Team — SP Designs Ltd Home About SP What We Do Meet the Team Portfolio The Beginning Residential Remodels Interior Design News Contact Us Home About SP What We Do Meet the Team Portfolio The Beginning Residential Remodels Interior Design News Contact Us The SP Design Team About SP What We Do Meet the Team SP Designs Ltd is a firm, formed in by Shannon Baumgartner, Senior Architectural Designer and Paul Baumgartner, Director of Operations Meet the Team Shannon Baumgartner Architectural Designer While completing her Bachelor’s degree in interior design and architecture, Shannon worked with other firms in Colorado, and traveled the world, drawing inspiration from a variety of architectural In launching SP Designs, she seeks to create an environment designed to best suite its individual user and further propel them in meeting their life Shannon is actively involved in the community, serving on the building committee, and as a board member, of Pikes Peak Habitat for Her home designs for Habitat for Humanity have been recognized by the mayor of Colorado Springs and featured on the local news Paul Baumgartner Director of Operations Paul’s architectural experience began as he assisted with finishing out the basement of his family’s home while in his He then worked several construction jobs from remodels, to framing, to roofing, to heating Here he observed the variety in architectural design across the years since the late ’s. Paul began sketching various floor plans as a teenager finally completing a full design of The Baumgartner Estate, in late Paul earned a business degree from Regis University, and though his main focus at SP Designs is business operations, he still provides creative input and assists with various other aspects of the design Contact us today to schedule a free consultation: Back to Top SP Designs Ltd, PO Box , Colorado Springs, CO , USA © SP Designs Ltd   Wayback Machine We will keep fighting for all libraries - stand with us! The particular module used in this tutorial, the , is capable of updating its position every second and communicates with an Arduino board using UART serial The uses the National Marine Electronics Association (NMEA) protocol which provides temporal and geolocation information such as Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), latitude, longitude, altitude, and approximate course The and Arduino board will also News Contact Us Loan Programs Fixed Rate Mortgages (FRM) The most common type of loan option, the traditional mortgage includes monthly principal and interest payments which never change during the loan’s The traditional fixed rate mortgage is the most common type of loan program, where monthly principal and interest payments never change during the life of the Fixed rate mortgages are available in terms ranging from to years and can be paid off at any time without This type of mortgage is structured, or "amortized" so that it will be completely paid off by the end of the loan There are also "bi-weekly" mortgages, which shorten the loan by calling for half the monthly payment every two (Since there are weeks in a year, you make payments, or "months" worth, every ) Even though you have a fixed rate mortgage, your monthly payment may vary if you have an "impound account". In addition to the monthly loan payment, some lenders collect additional money each month (from folks who put less than % cash down when purchasing their home) for the prorated monthly cost of property taxes and homeowners The extra money is put in an impound account by the lender who uses it to pay the borrowers property taxes and homeowners insurance premium when they are If either the property tax or the insurance happens to change, the borrower s monthly payment will be adjusted Howev

NY Tech Baseball Alumni Day Join us for the annual NY Tech Baseball Alumni Day on October , to help benefit Matt Our friend Matt McDevitt, a FDNY member of Ladder , has been out of work for almost two years fighting a rare cancer called NUT Midline Matt and his amazing wife, Jackie, have dedicated their lives to helping others: Matt as a firefighter and Jackie as a Physician They have a beautiful little boy, James, and recently had a baby Those of you who are lucky enough to know Matt and Jackie know they are nothing but relentless, positive and most of all resilient After multiple surgeries, rounds of chemo and rounds of radiation, Matt was recently accepted into a clinical trial at Dana Farber in He is currently commuting back and forth weekly to receive Matt was a teammate of Fund the First’s Robert Garland, Lou Bernardi, and John Eichhorn at NY Fund the First is conducting this fundraiser as a way to provide some financial relief as medical and travel related bills continue to pile The stress of unforeseen medical expenses should be the last thing they have to worry They are fierce and courageous and never ask for It is our hope that this effort will lift some of their stress so they can continue to fight and move Update: It is with deep sadness that Fund The First joins the McDevitt Family and the FDNY in announcing the passing of Firefighter Matthew McDevitt of who lost a hard fought battle with a rare cancer on Tuesday October , FF McDevitt leaves behind a wife and two young Our thoughts are with his family and friends during this difficult RAFFLE TICKETS Tickets cost $25 With each ticket purchase, contributors will receive a ticket number for a raffle that we will have at the alumni Buying a ticket is optional . Or send us an email at: For investors, feel free to check out our company profile on F6S, Founders Edge, , Crunchbase, or Spark Press Blog Terms Privacy Contact Education Teams Digital Badging Feedback Standards Contact Join the Beta About   Feedback Standards | Creative Critique Community Why Join How it Works Community Feedback Standards We get that opinions on creative work can be subjective, but how we go about giving feedback can help ensure quality, actionable advice for our Each post in our community contains: At least one specific project detail of what works well (25+ characters) At least one specific project detail of what can be improved (25+ characters) No expletives, vulgarity, or mature content No sales solicitations (optional) a version of your original image helping to explain the feedback provided If the feedback you receive doesn t meet these standards, report the feedback on our platform and our team will review the matter and resolve the Feedback Example A Quality Feedback Request Luxurious Project Attributes: Inclusive Project Audience: Age Age Hi guys! I m currently at the logo concept development phase for a project I m currently working on, so I m actually still exploring a lot of This is one direction that I will most probably include in the concept Will still narrow it down to one concept I was wondering what you guys think fit the brand the most, and if you guys have seen anything CONTEXT: Name: Amorene Jewelry Products: & Gold Feedback that should be approved looks like: What Works Well: ​ Love where you’re going with this concept - the the “A” and eternity theme is a good call in all your designs, I definitely see the inclusive I would recommend working with the third graphic option you posted because the flat bottom will be easy to center the store name beneath, and the layered outlines are more well balanced than the second & fourth ​ What Could Be Better: ​ One idea is to consider varying the line thickness to give the logo a more calligraphic feel, which I think would also help you hit on the luxurious Also, at a glance, the logo could feel more reminiscent of an “&” symbol than an “A”, maybe consider moving the pointed bottom center portion of the logo up just a tad to communicate more of a horizontal cross point like an “A” Hope that helps! Feedback that should be reported looks like: What Works Well: ​ They all look really good - I don t think you can go wrong with any of them! I personally like the third option the ​ What Could Be Better: ​ I honestly think the client would like all of these - keep up the great work! Press Blog Terms Privacy Contact Education Teams Digital Badging Feedback Standards Contact Join the Beta About   Research Behind Why Creatives Should Collaborate Why Join How it Works All Posts Search Nov , 4 min read Research Behind Why Creatives Should Collaborate Updated: Dec , Not all feedback is created Your mom means well when she tells you your third grade art class abstract work is flawless, and your roommate may really think your work is rockstar However, research shows that as a creative you get the most accurate and helpful feedback on your work from fellow creatives, and that you make better creative work when you give your peers feedback on their This give and get dynamic is exactly what we focus on here at Creative Why We Should GET Feedback from Fellow Creatives Why not just ? We are all plagued by false positives in our own work, or the belief that it is as good as it can If it could be better, we would simply make it While we may be able to perfect our work based on our experiences and perspective, our approach and interpretation of the work is limited to The more you work on a project, the greater your curse of knowledge you lose the ability to have a first impression of your Why not friends and family? A plethora of research presented in “The Mom Test”, which is used as Harvard curriculum, demonstrates that friends and family are more likely to lie to your face than provide actionable Friends and family have the best of intentions they believe in you and want to build you up, but just because you’re great doesn’t mean the first draft of your work Plus, no one wants to be the bearer of bad news (we believe feedback is good news, which we discuss here, but critique has a stigma of reflecting poorly on the creator). Telling someone their work is flawless preserves the personal relationship, and is an easier response than carefully analyzing work to recommend Plus, unless your friends and family are fellow creatives in your field, how actionable can their advice be beyond an initial visceral reaction to what you have created? January January Stepping into a New Beginning Hi Neighbors, Welcome to a new year and a new world! We hope you got our holiday card and that the start to your year has been safe and As our nation is changing and evolving, the Sustainable You team has been reflecting on how we can continually be the change and help others to do so as So far what we ve found is that it takes one step at time! Natalie Shares an Experience I just recently met Vicky and Jeff about a month ago through Craigslist during my housing search, who quickly became my housemates! On our very first encounter during the house tour, we discovered that we had a mutual friend, JS Ham, another team member here at Sustainable You! Jeff brought up the fact that he was about to get a Tesla in a couple days partially due to JS This was exciting news because they were already on track to becoming sustainable (check out our Tesla referral link and EV resources on our app )! One of the first steps towards a sustainable lifestyle begins with Jeff and Vicky mentioned how confusing recycling could be due to the lack of and or misleading information, such as mistaking resin identification codes on plastic packaging as a symbol to “toss this into the recycling bin”! What these mysterious codes found on the bottom of your orange juice bottle actually tell us is what type of plastic it’s composed of! Did you know? Compounds that are often a byproduct of refined crude oil are added to plastic products to manipulate its properties into being lighter, sturdier, or more There is a common misconception that if it’s made out of paper, plastic, glass, or aluminum, it s automatically recyclable, but this isn’t the case! Styrofoam and plastic bags, for example, are widely not accepted in curbside programs because they require special Ask us what to do with the filthy five! It has been an ongoing process of Jeff and Vicky asking all the right questions and myself explaining to them how recycling really works, what plastic resin codes mean, and what s recyclable and what s They have even shared their recycling journey with all of their friends ! In addition, I’ve seen a proactive effort to reduce food waste in the With my help, I get to eat leftovers as well which is always a plus! The food in our fridge has a pretty quick turnover rate if I must say so Lastly, takeout food being the main staples for Jeff and Vicky is now turning into home cooked Vicky just recently signed up for Arcadia as well after I walked them through the . Jeff’s sustainability score was and Vicky’s was , so there’s a lot of room for sustainable evolution ! “My first thought is I want to talk about how shocked I am about my It opened my eyes to how I can do better in caring for the environment, being sustainable, and getting rewarded to do I recommend the to everyone!” - It has been extremely rewarding to be a guide for Vicky and Jeff, who have been so open in learning how to adopt a more practice in their daily lives, and eager to share their journey and knowledge with everybody around Experience an with Natalie and our team Tax Credit Extended Great news - Congress was able to extend the % Tax credit until ! If you know any friends or family members that you would want to help get paid to go solar , please help us help them! Help a friend December November A Conscious Community Hi Neighbors, As we go into holiday season, we wanted to share our gratitude for how our community is Our work in awakening people to their power of evolving a sustainable consciousness means that we often find ourselves helping spiritual communities and houses of Largest Solar Install to Date! We installed on the Our Lady of Lebanon Maronite Church Seminary earlier this year and the next phases just broke We are grateful that they entrusted us to construct solar on their beautiful Church and Maronite House building on the other side of the This one took a while to get through permitting and interconnection, but we couldn’t be more excited to get it to the finish line! Help your Spiritual Center! Resilience and Regeneration It’s not just solar that we’ll be installing for churches either! History | MN Child Welfare Workforce Training Academy MNCWWC MN Child Welfare Workforce Collaborative MNCWTA MN Child Welfare Training Academy Menu About Us Toggle Dropdown Staff Advisory Structure History What s Coming Next Employment Training Toggle Dropdown Training Catalog Community Trainer Profiles Training Calendar News Regional Learning Center Toggle Dropdown Twin Cities Metro Learning Center Greater Minnesota Learning Centers Contact Us Staff Advisory Structure History What s Coming Next Employment History Scroll Left Critical media coverage of the child protection system Governor convenes Task Force Task Force Final Report and Recommendations Professional Development Work Group Proposes framework for Training Academy - First Workforce Stabilisation Study Reviews and Approves Practice Framework and competencies National Exploration of Training Partnerships Statewide focus groups on training framework Reports and Recommendations for Training System Reform Release of MN Realistic Job Preview Finalize and release Practice Framework and Competencies Passage of Child Welfare Training Legislation Scroll Right In Governor Mark Dayton established the Governor’s Task Force on the Protection of Children , which included representatives from the legislature, counties, doctors, attorneys, and education to examine child welfare in Minnesota and address the perceived In the Task Force concluded its work and released a final report and recommendations . Of the recommendations in that report, ten focused on reform to child welfare In September of , implementation workgroups of stakeholders were established, and a Professional Development workgroup focused on the recommendations that had to do with any form of training and education to new worker and supervisor In February of a Minnesota Child Welfare Workforce Stabilization Study was conducted to better understand the concerns of the child welfare workforce, with a particular focus on child protection professionals, in order to develop strategies to stabilize and strengthen the workforce in a time of The study was conducted by the Center for Advanced Studies in Child Welfare (CASCW) with support by the Center for Regional and Tribal Child Welfare Studies (CRTCWS) and county agency In March of the Professional Development workgroup finalized recommendations for a new training academy The workgroup identified that a strong state and university partnership would be critical in the implementation of Task Force During the spring and summer of there was a national exploration of training partnerships (Washington State, California, New Jersey, Colorado, Pennsylvania), followed by statewide stakeholder focus groups to better understand the training academy framework resulting in a Report and Recommendations for Training System Reform Through testimony in the and legislative sessions, a Bill was sponsored by House and Senate members of the Legislative Task Force on the Protection of Children, with the support of representatives Ron Kresha and Andrew The Bill passed and was funded in May A Joint Powers Agreement to create the MNCWTA became effective in September In December of that same year, the U of M Regents approved a lease agreement for a new Central Training Academy located in Roseville, In February demolition and renovation began with an anticipated completion in Find us on social media: The Minnesota Child Welfare Training Academy (MNCWTA) is a collaboration between the Child Safety and Permanency Division at the Department of Human Services (DHS) and the Center for Advanced Studies in Child Welfare (CASCW) at the University of Minnesota spaces at the discretion of the RESPONSE Some Collab Lab spaces may have additional rules in place, which will be made clearly available to Participants are responsible for knowing and abiding by rejected Gratuitous or sexual images or behaviour in spaces where they’re not Physical contact and simulated physical contact (e.g., textual descriptions such as “hug” or “backrub”) without consent or after a request to Threats of Incitement of violence towards any individual, including encouraging a person to commit suicide or to engage in Deliberate Stalking or Harassing photography or recording, including logging online activity for harassment Sustained disruption of Unwelcome sexual Pattern of inappropriate social contact, such as requesting assuming inappropriate levels of intimacy with Continued communication after requests to Deliberate “outing” of any aspect of a person’s identity without their consent except as necessary to protect vulnerable people from intentional Publication of private The Collab Lab prioritizes marginalized people’s safety over privileged people’s RESPONSE TEAM reserves the right not to act on complaints regarding the following: “Reverse”-isms, including “reverse racism,” “reverse sexism,” and “cisphobia”. With Trump’s signature on the Farm Bill, hemp gains federally legal President Donald Trump has signed hemp legalization into law, a change expected to unleash seismic market changes for the hemp Trump’s signature on the Farm Bill immediately removes hemp – defined cannabis below % THC – from the Controlled Substances The change also applies to extracts from hemp, including CBD and other Federal drug authorities will have to treat hemp like any other agricultural commodity, such as wheat or potatoes, and hemp farmers will no longer face legal or regulatory burdens of being classified as an illegal drug, such as difficulty getting crop insurance or barriers to getting ​ farm bill has removed hemp from the list of controlled substances, opening the floodgates for There is already a strong demand in the for products containing Cannabidiol, or CBD, a natural chemical component of cannabis and hemp that s , meaning it doesn t get you Companies offering CBD products have a tremendous opportunity, as proponents of CBD claim the substance offers , , and Consumers are already embracing CBD as a product to be incorporated into their daily CBD is popping up in a wide variety of products including oils, lotions, soaps, and beauty The newest niche is the food and beverage industry, where businesses have added it to snacks, coffee, ice cream, and By , CBD is expected to make its way into yogurts, soups, and even salad dressings, according to a report on food trends from Touted as a wonder drug capable of easing anxiety, reducing inflammation, and preventing seizures, cannabidiol, or CBD, has been growing rapidly in Following approval of the federal farm bill, the American hemp CBD market alone is projected to reach $20 billion by The Next Gold Rush Is the $22 Billion CBD Business "Creating environmental and medicinal " Home About Us Farm bill CBD PRODUCTS Contact Us View on Mobile
